This paper deals with Named Entity Recognition (NER) in social media data, which is a subfield of Natural Language Processing (NLP). Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which deals with NLP and related topics. The paper also uses machine learning techniques, which could fall under cs.LG (Machine Learning) or cs.IR (Information Retrieval). Additionally, the paper deals with social media data, which could fall under cs.SD (Social and Information Networks). Finally, the paper deals with Named Entity Recognition, which could fall under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
